From: "Benjamin A. Beasley" <code@musicinmybrain.net>
Date: Tue, 13 May 2025 07:09:41 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?Downstream-only:=20Ignore=20a=20few=20tests=20w?=
 =?UTF-8?q?e=20can=E2=80=99t=20compile?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

These tests fail to compile with:

  error[E0277]: the trait bound `Cow<'a, str>: ZeroFrom<'a, str>` is not satisfied

This problem seems to be specific to testing the released crate; we
cannot reproduce it in a git checkout. Enabling all features does not
help; nor does ensuring the zerofrom dependency with the derive feature
is present in the normalized Cargo.toml, as in
https://github.com/unicode-org/icu4x/pull/6585. It could still be a
similar issue with path dev-depencencies that we haven’t found yet. See
https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/rust-zerovec/pull-request/1#comment-232114
and subsequent discussion.
---
 src/lib.rs     | 4 ++--
 src/map/map.rs | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/lib.rs b/src/lib.rs
index aac65cde9..8c2089187 100644
--- a/src/lib.rs
+++ b/src/lib.rs
@@ -89,7 +89,7 @@
 //!
 //! Use custom types inside of ZeroVec:
 //!
-//! ```rust
+//! ```rust,ignore
 //! # #[cfg(all(feature = "serde", feature = "derive"))] {
 //! use zerovec::{ZeroVec, VarZeroVec, ZeroMap};
 //! use std::borrow::Cow;
@@ -463,7 +463,7 @@ pub use zerovec_derive::make_ule;
 ///
 /// # Example
 ///
-/// ```rust
+/// ```rust,ignore
 /// use std::borrow::Cow;
 /// use zerofrom::ZeroFrom;
 /// use zerovec::ule::encode_varule_to_box;
diff --git a/src/map/map.rs b/src/map/map.rs
index 1dc974125..176029df1 100644
--- a/src/map/map.rs
+++ b/src/map/map.rs
@@ -414,7 +414,7 @@ where
     /// Same as `insert()`, but allows using [EncodeAsVarULE](crate::ule::EncodeAsVarULE)
     /// types with the value to avoid an extra allocation when dealing with custom ULE types.
     ///
-    /// ```rust
+    /// ```rust,ignore
     /// use std::borrow::Cow;
     /// use zerovec::ZeroMap;
     ///
-- 
